SIMPLE: polling
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Polling
<hw>Poll"ing</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[See <er>Poll</er>
the head.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The act of topping, lopping, or
cropping, as trees or hedges.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Plunder, or extortion.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>E. Hall.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>The act of voting, or of registering a
vote.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Polling booth</b></col>, <cd>a temporary structure where
the voting at an election is done; a polling place.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Polliniferous</ent>⟦br⟧
